       <p>&nbsp;</p> 
       <p align="justify"><font size="2" face="Georgia, Times New Roman, Times, serif">The Feathered Sun... is found on buffalo hides used as cloaks and occasionally as a background for ceremonies. The Sun is composed of concentric circles formed of stylized eagle feathers; the resulting impression is particularly evocative in that the symbol simultaneously suggests center, radiation, power, and majesty. (<em>The Feathered Sun: Plains Indians in Art and Philosophy</em> [Bloomington, IN: World Wisdom Books, 1990], p. 100.)</font></p> 
